name: AnalgesicsForAcutePainParenteralRoute
title: Analgesics for Acute Pain (Parenteral Route)
purpose: (Clinical Focus: The purpose of this value set is to represent concepts that represent analgesic medications for the treatment of acute pain. This value set is a subset of “Analgesics for Acute Pain” value set that only includes medications that are administered via a parenteral route.),(Data Element Scope: This value set may use a model element related to Medication.),(Inclusion Criteria: Includes concepts that represent generic, human use, and prescribable analgesic medications for the treatment of acute pain that are administered via a parenteral route and that have a Semantic Clinical Drug (SCD) or Generic Pack (GPCK) term type in the RxNorm code system.),(Exclusion Criteria: Excludes concepts that represent analgesic medications for acute pain that are not administered via a parenteral route for the treatment of acute pain.)
